{"title":"Blender tutorial: advanced modeling","description":"In this new post of the series Blender tutorial I will talk about advanced modeling in Blender.","date":"21 Aug 2018","readingTime":"6 min read","featuredImageUrl":"/static/46e9e010146783b5f8008ee302e278d1/blender-add-modifier.jpg","authors":["fabrizio_duroni"],"tags":["computer graphics","blender"],"math":false,"content":"<p><em>In this new post of the series Blender tutorial I will talk about advanced modeling in Blender.</em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>In the <a href=\"/2018/06/02/blender-tutorial-4-modeling-basics-part-2/\">previous post of the series \"Blender tutorial\"</a> we\ntalked about the basics of modeling in Blender. In this post we will study Blender advanced modeling tools.<br>\nLet's start from <strong>modifiers</strong>. All the operation we saw in the previous modeling post were all \"one time operation\":\nafter we apply them we can't change their properties to modify the result we obtain. Modifiers let us apply modification\nto a mesh that is possible to revert, modify and preview. When we are sure about the result, we can apply the modifier\nto get the mesh modification we want.<br>\nWe can apply a modifier by selecting an object (right click on it) and go under the properties panel and <em>click on the\nwrench icon</em>. Here we can select a modifier from the list <em>Add modifier</em>.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/46e9e010146783b5f8008ee302e278d1/c58a3/blender-add-modifier.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The add modifier feature\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/46e9e010146783b5f8008ee302e278d1/0470c/blender-add-modifier.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/46e9e010146783b5f8008ee302e278d1/6c669/blender-add-modifier.jpg 285w,\n/static/46e9e010146783b5f8008ee302e278d1/882a4/blender-add-modifier.jpg 570w,\n/static/46e9e010146783b5f8008ee302e278d1/0470c/blender-add-modifier.jpg 1140w,\n/static/46e9e010146783b5f8008ee302e278d1/c58a3/blender-add-modifier.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The add modifier feature</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>For example let's try to add a simple deform to a cube. After adding it we see our cube deformed. We can than tweak the\nparameters of the deformation as we prefer. Each modifier as its own properties, based of which type of modification it\napplies to the mesh. Anyway there are some common button to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>show/hide the modifier result during rendering</em></li>\n<li><em>show/hide the modifier result in the 3D window</em></li>\n<li><em>show/hide the modifier result in the 3D window in Edit mode</em></li>\n<li><em>show/hide the cage of the modifier in the 3D window</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d017510311601cae5512cd24797b2cdb/c58a3/blender-add-modifier-icons.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The add modifier panel\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/d017510311601cae5512cd24797b2cdb/0470c/blender-add-modifier-icons.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d017510311601cae5512cd24797b2cdb/6c669/blender-add-modifier-icons.jpg 285w,\n/static/d017510311601cae5512cd24797b2cdb/882a4/blender-add-modifier-icons.jpg 570w,\n/static/d017510311601cae5512cd24797b2cdb/0470c/blender-add-modifier-icons.jpg 1140w,\n/static/d017510311601cae5512cd24797b2cdb/c58a3/blender-add-modifier-icons.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The add modifier panel</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>After that we have the <strong>subdivision surface</strong>. As stated on Wikipedia, subdivision surface is a technique discovered\nsimultaneously by Edwin Catmull and Jim Clark:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A subdivision surface, in the field of 3D computer graphics, is a method of representing a smooth surface via the specification of a coarser piecewise linear polygon mesh. The smooth surface can be calculated from the coarse mesh as the limit of recursive subdivision of each polygonal face into smaller faces that better approximate the smooth surface.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This basically means that with subdivision surface we can approximate smoother surfaces starting from another one.<br>\nIn Blender we can apply <em>subdivision surface as a modifier</em>.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6efe41719e3fbff2c75e01600415aff8/c58a3/blender-add-subdivision-surface.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The add subdivision surface feature\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/6efe41719e3fbff2c75e01600415aff8/0470c/blender-add-subdivision-surface.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6efe41719e3fbff2c75e01600415aff8/6c669/blender-add-subdivision-surface.jpg 285w,\n/static/6efe41719e3fbff2c75e01600415aff8/882a4/blender-add-subdivision-surface.jpg 570w,\n/static/6efe41719e3fbff2c75e01600415aff8/0470c/blender-add-subdivision-surface.jpg 1140w,\n/static/6efe41719e3fbff2c75e01600415aff8/c58a3/blender-add-subdivision-surface.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The add subdivision surface feature</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>After the subdivision is applied it is possible to modify the mesh only on the original edges and faces of the mesh. In\nfact this elements will be the only one that we can select from our mesh.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9e306764b7f1a5cef09b3ece3dc9a694/c58a3/blender-added-subdivision-surface.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.80701754385966%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The result of adding subdivision surface to the mesh\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/9e306764b7f1a5cef09b3ece3dc9a694/0470c/blender-added-subdivision-surface.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9e306764b7f1a5cef09b3ece3dc9a694/6c669/blender-added-subdivision-surface.jpg 285w,\n/static/9e306764b7f1a5cef09b3ece3dc9a694/882a4/blender-added-subdivision-surface.jpg 570w,\n/static/9e306764b7f1a5cef09b3ece3dc9a694/0470c/blender-added-subdivision-surface.jpg 1140w,\n/static/9e306764b7f1a5cef09b3ece3dc9a694/c58a3/blender-added-subdivision-surface.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The result of adding subdivision surface to the mesh</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Another interesting modifier is the <strong>mirror modifier</strong>. It is especially useful when you need to do Symmetric modeling.\nAfter applying this modifier every operation you made on one side of your mesh will be mirrored on the other side. For\nthis reason, especially when you're modeling some character/organic mesh, it is useful to delete one side of the mesh\nand mirror the other one (with all the modification you do). In the option of the modifier you can choose on which axis\nthe mirroring must be applied.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bbfe3844205bfe4442f90eb374561c2a/c58a3/blender-mirror-modifier.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The mirror modifier\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/bbfe3844205bfe4442f90eb374561c2a/0470c/blender-mirror-modifier.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bbfe3844205bfe4442f90eb374561c2a/6c669/blender-mirror-modifier.jpg 285w,\n/static/bbfe3844205bfe4442f90eb374561c2a/882a4/blender-mirror-modifier.jpg 570w,\n/static/bbfe3844205bfe4442f90eb374561c2a/0470c/blender-mirror-modifier.jpg 1140w,\n/static/bbfe3844205bfe4442f90eb374561c2a/c58a3/blender-mirror-modifier.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The mirror modifier</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>The last interesting modifier (for now) we will see it is the <strong>boolean modifier</strong>. This modifier let us modify meshes\nby calculate difference, union and intersection between them.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/74f45fa6663b6d4f3264ff3003358d39/c58a3/blender-boolean-modifier.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The boolean modifier\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/74f45fa6663b6d4f3264ff3003358d39/0470c/blender-boolean-modifier.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/74f45fa6663b6d4f3264ff3003358d39/6c669/blender-boolean-modifier.jpg 285w,\n/static/74f45fa6663b6d4f3264ff3003358d39/882a4/blender-boolean-modifier.jpg 570w,\n/static/74f45fa6663b6d4f3264ff3003358d39/0470c/blender-boolean-modifier.jpg 1140w,\n/static/74f45fa6663b6d4f3264ff3003358d39/c58a3/blender-boolean-modifier.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The boolean modifier</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4cf1415dae91a065dd22818809654347/c58a3/blender-boolean-modifier-operation-option.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The boolean modifier options\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4cf1415dae91a065dd22818809654347/0470c/blender-boolean-modifier-operation-option.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4cf1415dae91a065dd22818809654347/6c669/blender-boolean-modifier-operation-option.jpg 285w,\n/static/4cf1415dae91a065dd22818809654347/882a4/blender-boolean-modifier-operation-option.jpg 570w,\n/static/4cf1415dae91a065dd22818809654347/0470c/blender-boolean-modifier-operation-option.jpg 1140w,\n/static/4cf1415dae91a065dd22818809654347/c58a3/blender-boolean-modifier-operation-option.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The boolean modifier options</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Another interesting tool is the <strong>\"Loop Cut and Slide\"</strong>. With this option we can add edge loops to our mesh. This tool\nis useful especially when you need to have more mesh polygon to model the mesh details you want.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b25bcaf3b4b8b7b383d1aabe020013b6/c58a3/blender-loop-edge-and-slide.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The loop edge and slide tool\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/b25bcaf3b4b8b7b383d1aabe020013b6/0470c/blender-loop-edge-and-slide.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b25bcaf3b4b8b7b383d1aabe020013b6/6c669/blender-loop-edge-and-slide.jpg 285w,\n/static/b25bcaf3b4b8b7b383d1aabe020013b6/882a4/blender-loop-edge-and-slide.jpg 570w,\n/static/b25bcaf3b4b8b7b383d1aabe020013b6/0470c/blender-loop-edge-and-slide.jpg 1140w,\n/static/b25bcaf3b4b8b7b383d1aabe020013b6/c58a3/blender-loop-edge-and-slide.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The loop edge and slide tool</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Then we have the <strong>joining mesh tool</strong> and the <strong>stitching vertices tool</strong>. For the first one, as the name suggest, you\ncan combine multiple mesh into a single one in blender. To join two or more meshes, we have to select them while we are\nobject mode. Remember: the last one selected will be the mesh to which the other ones will be joined. After that we can\napply the join mesh using:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>the menu option Object -> Join</em></li>\n<li><em>the shortcut \"ctrl + j keys\"</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4f1a2c88764a694f9e45a97a7b0e11c3/c58a3/blender-join-meshes.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Join meshes tool\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4f1a2c88764a694f9e45a97a7b0e11c3/0470c/blender-join-meshes.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4f1a2c88764a694f9e45a97a7b0e11c3/6c669/blender-join-meshes.jpg 285w,\n/static/4f1a2c88764a694f9e45a97a7b0e11c3/882a4/blender-join-meshes.jpg 570w,\n/static/4f1a2c88764a694f9e45a97a7b0e11c3/0470c/blender-join-meshes.jpg 1140w,\n/static/4f1a2c88764a694f9e45a97a7b0e11c3/c58a3/blender-join-meshes.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Join meshes tool</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>After joining two or more meshes, we will need to fill the gap between then. We can do that by using the <strong>merge tool</strong>,\nthe <strong>remove double tool</strong> and the <strong>snap element tool</strong> to stitch the vertices that are on the border of the meshes.\nThe vertices must be open: they need to be without a connection on one side. So after selecting one vertex we can snap\nit using the snap element tool. We can activate it using the button in the bottom bar of the 3D window. After activating\nit we can grab the selected vertex by pressing the <em>g key</em>, and snap it to our target vertex.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/185894d783a52043acb37d0e453ff36e/c58a3/blender-snap-element.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Snap element tool\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/185894d783a52043acb37d0e453ff36e/0470c/blender-snap-element.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/185894d783a52043acb37d0e453ff36e/6c669/blender-snap-element.jpg 285w,\n/static/185894d783a52043acb37d0e453ff36e/882a4/blender-snap-element.jpg 570w,\n/static/185894d783a52043acb37d0e453ff36e/0470c/blender-snap-element.jpg 1140w,\n/static/185894d783a52043acb37d0e453ff36e/c58a3/blender-snap-element.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Snap element tool</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>After snapping vertices we have to <strong>remove duplicates</strong>. We can do it using the merge tool or using the remove doubles\ntool. We can find these tools:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>under Mesh -> Type of element under selection</em></li>\n<li>from the contextual menu that you can show by using the shortcut <em>ctrl + v key</em> for vertices (NB.: there are also\ncontextual menus for faces and edges that we can show using <em>ctrl + f key</em> and <em>ctrl + e key</em>)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If we decide to go with the remove doubles tools, after applying the operation a popup at the top of the 3D window will\nappear that will tell us the number of duplicated vertices removed.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/98e4202181c6edc52bc2fa96e5f645a5/c58a3/blender-merge-remove-tools.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Merge remove tools\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/98e4202181c6edc52bc2fa96e5f645a5/0470c/blender-merge-remove-tools.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/98e4202181c6edc52bc2fa96e5f645a5/6c669/blender-merge-remove-tools.jpg 285w,\n/static/98e4202181c6edc52bc2fa96e5f645a5/882a4/blender-merge-remove-tools.jpg 570w,\n/static/98e4202181c6edc52bc2fa96e5f645a5/0470c/blender-merge-remove-tools.jpg 1140w,\n/static/98e4202181c6edc52bc2fa96e5f645a5/c58a3/blender-merge-remove-tools.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Merge remove tools</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>In blender it is <strong>possible to model also text</strong>. We can add text by selecting <em>Add -> Text</em>. We can modify the text by\nselecting the edit mode: a text cursor will appear so that we can modify the text. In the property panel a special tab\nwill let as customize the text property.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/13889cc78e5f646fa6b5864a62e844df/c58a3/blender-add-text.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Add text to a scene\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/13889cc78e5f646fa6b5864a62e844df/0470c/blender-add-text.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/13889cc78e5f646fa6b5864a62e844df/6c669/blender-add-text.jpg 285w,\n/static/13889cc78e5f646fa6b5864a62e844df/882a4/blender-add-text.jpg 570w,\n/static/13889cc78e5f646fa6b5864a62e844df/0470c/blender-add-text.jpg 1140w,\n/static/13889cc78e5f646fa6b5864a62e844df/c58a3/blender-add-text.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Add text to a scene</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cccd2de76873d190bcde6b106e3049aa/c58a3/blender-text-properties.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Add text properties\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/cccd2de76873d190bcde6b106e3049aa/0470c/blender-text-properties.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cccd2de76873d190bcde6b106e3049aa/6c669/blender-text-properties.jpg 285w,\n/static/cccd2de76873d190bcde6b106e3049aa/882a4/blender-text-properties.jpg 570w,\n/static/cccd2de76873d190bcde6b106e3049aa/0470c/blender-text-properties.jpg 1140w,\n/static/cccd2de76873d190bcde6b106e3049aa/c58a3/blender-text-properties.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Add text properties</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Last but not least is the <strong>vertex groups tool</strong>. This tool allows us to save selection of vertices so that we are able\nto select them later. We can create a vertex group in the property panel in the corresponding tab. In this tab we have\nbuttons to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>add/remove vertices to a group</em></li>\n<li><em>select/deselect the vertices of a group</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/17b3c43dc10ec60875d1555b641af32b/c58a3/blender-vertex-group.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The vertex group tool\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/17b3c43dc10ec60875d1555b641af32b/0470c/blender-vertex-group.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/17b3c43dc10ec60875d1555b641af32b/6c669/blender-vertex-group.jpg 285w,\n/static/17b3c43dc10ec60875d1555b641af32b/882a4/blender-vertex-group.jpg 570w,\n/static/17b3c43dc10ec60875d1555b641af32b/0470c/blender-vertex-group.jpg 1140w,\n/static/17b3c43dc10ec60875d1555b641af32b/c58a3/blender-vertex-group.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The vertex group tool</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>In the next post we will discuss about outliner, layers, groups, hierarchies and scenes.</p>"}